---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Giscus from '../components/Giscus.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const VERSION = '3.6.2';
const baseUrl = `https://github.com/zhitongblog/solomd/releases/download/v${VERSION}`;
---

<Layout
  title="What's new in SoloMD v3.6"
  description="Live-edit image and table inline rendering (#44) — the long-standing live-edit gap is closed. Plus 5 polish fixes batched in: AI button routing, image export crop-to-content, optional watermark, folder picker memory, and Mac toolbar overflow. (v3.6.1 hotfix patches two regressions discovered after v3.6.0 shipped — image export and toolbar dropdowns are working again.)"
  lang={lang}
>
  <Header lang={lang} />
  <main>
    <article class="container whats-new">
      <nav class="breadcrumbs">
        <a href="/">Home</a> / <span>What's new</span>
      </nav>

      <p class="version-row">
        <span class="version-tag">v{VERSION}</span>
        <time>April 2026</time>
      </p>
      <h1>Live-edit blocks, plus 5 polish fixes.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        v3.6 closes the long-standing live-edit gap (<strong>image &
        table inline rendering</strong>, issue #44) and bundles
        <strong>five polish fixes</strong> batched in from rapid
        feedback after v3.5.5. v3.6.1 is a hotfix patch for two
        regressions caught the same day v3.6.0 went out — both fully
        reverted, see below.
      </p>

      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href={`${baseUrl}/SoloMD_${VERSION}_universal.dmg`}>⬇ Download v{VERSION} (Mac)</a>
        <a class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg" href={`${baseUrl}/SoloMD_${VERSION}_x64_en-US.msi`}>Download (Windows)</a>
        <a class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg" href={`https://github.com/zhitongblog/solomd/releases/tag/v${VERSION}`}>All assets →</a>
      </div>

      <section>
        <h2>🔨 #44 — Live-edit image & table block widgets</h2>
        <p>
          In live-edit view (the toolbar's pen-on-paper icon), markdown
          source has rich formatting applied inline. Until v3.6, two
          block-level kinds didn't render in place:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>A line whose <em>entire content</em> is an image (<code>![alt](url)</code> with no surrounding prose) collapses to an actual <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> widget. Image source resolves through the same pipeline as the Preview pane.</li>
          <li>A header row + separator + at least one body row collapses to a real <code>&lt;table&gt;</code>, rendered through markdown-it.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Both widgets unmount the moment the cursor enters any line
          inside the matched block range — no view-mode switch needed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>✅ Five polish fixes</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>AI button → wrong settings location.</strong> Toolbar AI fallback now opens the <em>Integrations</em> tab directly, not the default <em>Basics</em>.</li>
          <li><strong>Image export crop-to-content.</strong> Short notes export at their actual rendered height, not with empty space below.</li>
          <li><strong>"Created with SoloMD" watermark — now a setting.</strong> Default ON for mild brand visibility; toggle off in <strong>Settings → Export</strong>.</li>
          <li><strong>Folder picker remembers last workspace.</strong> The OS folder dialog now opens at the workspace SoloMD already has loaded.</li>
          <li><strong>Mac narrow-window toolbar overflow.</strong> Right-side critical buttons (AI / Sponsor / Settings) reachable at any window width. <em>(Note: this fix was reverted in v3.6.1 — see below.)</em></li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>🩹 v3.6.1 hotfix</h2>
        <p>
          Two regressions made it past my v3.6.0 self-test. Both fully
          reverted in v3.6.1, shipped same day:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Image export blank.</strong> Universal — not just
            Windows. The new <code>windowWidth/Height</code> hint to
            html2canvas conflicted with the off-screen render trick;
            output came back blank. Reverted to default html2canvas
            auto-sizing. The crop-to-content concern was already
            handled by the watermark toggle (footer + bottom padding).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Toolbar dropdowns clicked through to editor.</strong>
            Every dropdown — New / Open / Insert / Copy / Export —
            opened but clicks fell through to the editor below. The
            <code>overflow-x: auto</code> rule on <code>.toolbar</code>
            (added for the Mac narrow-window fix #181) caused browsers
            to escalate <code>overflow-y</code> to clip too. Reverted;
            #181 is re-queued for v3.7 with a <code>&lt;Teleport&gt;</code>-based
            dropdown approach that doesn't need overflow on the
            toolbar.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Self-test is now a hard step before any tag push — both
          flows verified in a real browser session before v3.6.1
          went out.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>🔮 What's next — v3.7</h2>
        <p>
          Top of the queue: re-do the Mac narrow-window menu fix
          properly (with <code>&lt;Teleport&gt;</code>), iPad / Mac
          App Store resubmission, and whatever lands in
          <a href="https://github.com/zhitongblog/solomd/discussions">Discussions</a>
          + <a href="https://github.com/zhitongblog/solomd/issues">issues</a>
          over the next cycle.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="thanks-row">
        Thanks <strong>@beihai23</strong> (PR #48 in v3.5.5) and
        <strong>@sparkdonn-netizen</strong> (#43 screenshots) for the
        prior cycle. Earlier: <a href="/blog/">browse the blog →</a>
      </p>
    </article>
    <Giscus lang={lang} />
  </main>
  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>

<style>
  .whats-new { max-width: 820px; padding: 40px 20px 80px; }
  .breadcrumbs { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .breadcrumbs a { color: inherit; }
  .version-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .version-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #000;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .whats-new time { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .whats-new h1 { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem); line-height: 1.1; margin: 0 0 22px; }
  .whats-new h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 1.9rem); margin: 56px 0 16px; }
  .whats-new .lead { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .whats-new p { line-height: 1.75; margin: 12px 0; }
  .whats-new ul, .whats-new ol { padding-left: 22px; }
  .whats-new li { margin: 6px 0; line-height: 1.7; }
  .whats-new code {
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.92em;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--accent-deep);
  }
  .whats-new a:not(.btn) { color: var(--accent); }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 28px 0 8px;
  }
  .thanks-row {
    margin-top: 64px;
    padding-top: 22px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>
